&lt;h2 id=&#34;next&#34;&gt;Next&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So far I&amp;rsquo;ve been able to go without Sparrow and iTerm, but it hasn&amp;rsquo;t been easy. If I go the distance with Terminal.app and/or Mail.app I&amp;rsquo;ll probably write up a little something about it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let me know if you&amp;rsquo;re interested in that or not. I&amp;rsquo;ve been running low on writing time lately!&lt;/p&gt;

      &lt;p&gt;Spring is in the air and a shiny new 13&amp;quot; MacBook Pro is in my office&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It will replace the mid-2011 13&amp;quot; MacBook Air that I&amp;rsquo;m writing this post with. Why aren&amp;rsquo;t I writing it on my new machine? Because for the first time ever I&amp;rsquo;ve decided &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; to migrate. My current install has been through 6 major operating system upgrades, countless experiments, untold hacks, and more. It&amp;rsquo;s time to start fresh.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt=&#34;Dual Wielding&#34; src=&#34;http://jerodsanto.net/drop/macs-side-by-side.jpg&#34; style=&#34;max-width: 400px&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ll be running the two machines side-by-side for the next couple weeks, only loading things I need on to the new one. This means every app has to prove itself to me again. No exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;apps&#34;&gt;Apps&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I plan to write up a few posts as I make the transition, documenting what makes the cut and what doesn&amp;rsquo;t. This post covers the instant installs that I didn&amp;rsquo;t hesitate to install on day one. Since this is a work machine, these apps are all Serious Business‚Ñ¢. You won&amp;rsquo;t find games or family tree software in this lot. These apps help me make a living.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt=&#34;This pic might be my first and last real use for LaunchPad&#34; src=&#34;http://jerodsanto.net/drop/instant-installs.png&#34; style=&#34;max-width: 512px;&#34;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://dropbox.com&#34;&gt;Dropbox&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äî For file sync and sharing, accept no substitutes. It&amp;rsquo;s an amazing feeling to load up a new machine with Dropbox, wait a few minutes, and have all my most critical files downloaded and right where I left them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://sublimetext.com/3&#34;&gt;Sublime Text&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äî Speaking of dual wielding, I&amp;rsquo;m one of those weirdos who uses two text editors: Vim and Sublime Text. ST 3 is an excellent editor, and I&amp;rsquo;m excited to see its author back from hiatus and making progress once again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://google.com/chrome&#34;&gt;Chrome&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äî I fell out of love with Chrome as a day-to-day browser&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:2&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:2&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;, but it still has best-in-class Dev Tools, which is the only reason it makes the cut.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://rogueamoeba.com/audiohijack/&#34;&gt;Audio Hijack&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äî Because podcasting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://kapeli.com/dash&#34;&gt;Dash&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äî The best documentation browser I&amp;rsquo;ve ever used. I almost forgot that it also makes docs available offline until a recent trip to the boondocks reminded me. So great.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.acqualia.com/soulver/&#34;&gt;Soulver&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äî I always have one or two Soulver sheets open while working. It sits in the sweet spot between Spotlight math and a full-on spreadsheet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://manytricks.com/moom/&#34;&gt;Moom&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äî I wish I didn&amp;rsquo;t need Moom. OS X should handle window management better&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:3&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:3&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;, but it doesn&amp;rsquo;t. Moom fixes it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://slack.com&#34;&gt;Slack&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äî Slack is team communication done right. Their Mac app, like everything else, is an absolute joy to use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
