&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    doc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#1f2328&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;url&lt;span style=&#34;color:#1f2328&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;puts&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;The request for a page at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;url&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt; timed out...skipping.&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;next&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now we safely output the offending error and continue with the next value in the urls array. That‚Äôs naace!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The truth is that this will not catch all exceptions. The problem is that when using the open-uri class you can receive an &lt;code&gt;OpenURI::Error&lt;/code&gt; if the site you‚Äôre trying to access returns a 404, 403, 500 or other ‚Äúnot good‚Äù response, and you can receive a &lt;code&gt;Timeout::Error&lt;/code&gt; if the site simply doesn‚Äôt respond at all and the request times out. Let‚Äôs modify our nugget to handle both scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ruby&#34; data-lang=&#34;ruby&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;require&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;open-uri&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;urls &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;%w[ http://slashdot.org/ http://news.ycombinator.com/ http://www.techmeme.com/ ]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;urls&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;each &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;url&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    doc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#1f2328&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;url&lt;span style=&#34;color:#1f2328&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;Timeout&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;Error&lt;/span&gt;
