&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;div &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;container&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;      &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;p&lt;/span&gt; style&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;color: green&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;%= flash[:notice] %&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;      &amp;lt;%=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;yield&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#032f62&#34;&gt;:main&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;%&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;    &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;/body&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span&gt;html&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The key here is the &lt;code&gt;yield :main&lt;/code&gt; which means we can use &lt;code&gt;content_for&lt;/code&gt; to put our nested layouts‚Äô output inside the yield. Here is the &lt;code&gt;lists&lt;/code&gt; layout:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ruby&#34; data-lang=&#34;ruby&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#57606a&#34;&gt;# lists.html.erb&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;% content_for &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#032f62&#34;&gt;:main&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;%&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;  &amp;lt;div id=&amp;#34;lists_container&amp;#34;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;%= yield %&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;  &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;% end %&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;%=&lt;/span&gt; render &lt;span style=&#34;color:#032f62&#34;&gt;:file&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;layouts/application.html.erb&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;%&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now your view gets rendered inside this layout‚Äôs &lt;code&gt;yield&lt;/code&gt; and its all good in the hood. Cheers!&lt;/p&gt;

      &lt;p&gt;Securing your &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.slicehost.com&#34;&gt;slice&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=&#34;http://firehol.sourceforge.net&#34;&gt;FireHOL&lt;/a&gt; is a really, really good move. Here are a few notes that may save you some time:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FireHOL requires a kernel config to know which modules to load, SliceHost uses Xen, so to get the kernel configuration in the right place, execute the following commands:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;/proc/config.gz ~ &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; ~
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;gunzip config.gz &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; mv config /boot/config-&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;uname -r&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0a3069&#34;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;FireHOL ships with a safety net configured in &lt;code&gt;/etc/defaults/firehol&lt;/code&gt;. It will not start until you edit this file and change this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#953800&#34;&gt;START_FIREHOL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;NO
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;to this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#953800&#34;&gt;START_FIREHOL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;YES
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;That should do it for gotchas. Now you can lock down your machine to assure you‚Äôre only serving what you expect. Fore more on configuring FireHOL, check out their &lt;a href=&#34;http://firehol.sourceforge.net/tutorial.html&#34;&gt;online tutorial&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

      &lt;p&gt;If you‚Äôve been hacking at your linux CLI for a little while, you‚Äôre probably familiar with the pic below. If not, just type &lt;code&gt;top&lt;/code&gt; and your terminal will spring to life with an ever-updating process and usage display.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/wp-content/uploads/2008/06/top.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;top&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While very useful, &lt;code&gt;top&lt;/code&gt;‚Äôs output is oogly. It‚Äôs the 21st century already! Let‚Äôs use some colors!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thankfully, &lt;code&gt;htop&lt;/code&gt; is here to save the day. To install on a Debian-based linux, simply type:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt-get install htop
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;now we should have &lt;code&gt;htop&lt;/code&gt; installed. Let‚Äôs add a quick alias so we don‚Äôt accidentally launch &lt;code&gt;top&lt;/code&gt; anymore. Open your &lt;code&gt;.bashrc&lt;/code&gt; in your favorite editor and add the following code to it:&lt;/p&gt;
